--- 
title  : Ratch
summary: Ruby-based Batch Scripting
contact: trans <transfire@gmail.com>

requires:
  - syckle (build)
  - qed (test)

description:
  Ratch is a Ruby-based batch scripting language.
  It's a DSL over regular RUby to make the life
  of the batch script writter easier.

  Integrated set of a path-related libraries

  Path is all about paths. It's provides a reimplementation of the Ruby
  standard Pathname library, Path::Name, a superior globbing
  facility, Path::List and an isolated shell-evironment, Path::Shell.

